.TH "ice_trigger_vf_reset" 9 "ice_trigger_vf_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_trigger_vf_reset \- Reset a VF on HW
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ice_trigger_vf_reset
.BI "(struct ice_vf *vf "  ","
.BI "bool is_vflr "  ","
.BI "bool is_pfr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vf" 12
pointer to the VF structure
.IP "is_vflr" 12
true if VFLR was issued, false if not
.IP "is_pfr" 12
true if the reset was triggered due to a previous PFR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Trigger hardware to start a reset for a particular VF. Expects the caller
to wait the proper amount of time to allow hardware to reset the VF before
it cleans up and restores VF functionality.
